<promed-mena@promedmail.org>

[There are no reports of significant cultures from any affected patients, but certainly campylobacteriosis could be a cause. Enterococci are generally not considered to be foodborne pathogens.

Shawarma is a dish in Middle Eastern cuisine consisting of meat cut into thin slices, stacked in a cone-like shape, and roasted on a slowly turning vertical rotisserie or spit. Originally made of lamb or mutton, today's shawarma may also be chicken, turkey, beef, or veal.

The symptoms related to the illness are not stated nor is the time from food ingestion until the development of symptoms. - Mod.LL

HealthMap/ProMED map:
Balqa Governorate, Jordan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7637947,25328]
